also <@755590043632140352> you do have #5222 implemented **but only** if you process the block `beacon-chain/blockchain/process_block.go:650-659`
```go
for _, att := range atts {
        root := bytesutil.ToBytes32(att.Data.BeaconBlockRoot)
        if !s.cfg.ForkChoiceStore.HasNode(root) {
            continue
        }
        for i := range committee {
            if att.AggregationBits.BitAt(uint64(i)) {
                s.cfg.ForkChoiceStore.SetPTCVote(root, uint64(i), att.Data.PayloadPresent, att.Data.BlobDataAvailable)
            }
        }
    }
```
this solves the mystery, due to the fact that `deathstar` is packing ptc votes, prysm correctly counts them when processing the block per #5222

however prysm doesn't follow #5222 when
- (1) processing ptc attestations from gossip
- (2) and when prysm is producing blocks, you are not setting the aggregate bits correctly

I will patch `deathstar` tomorrow to not pack ptc attestations that vote against it's own payload reorg, we should then see prysm being a `deathstar` supporter
